{
  "stem": "11611.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was Sunday afternoon, December 7, obviously.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a bunch of students were congregated around the central desk of the library, so I finally decided I'd quit typing notes and go down and find out what was going on.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And somebody said the Japanese had bombed Pearl Harbor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, it was a surprise.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The concrete event was a surprise.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I had started studying Japanese extra-curricularly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was in law school in the Harvard College in September of that year, which was about three months before the war, which was probably a little foresighted.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I took courses there with a fellow named Reischauer, who later became ambassador to Japan.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I should say it affected my education.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It affected my outlook, too, beyond my education.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As soon as-- as soon as the war was declared, the question was what part of the military was I going to go into?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, the law school took the same view.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They-- the second year in law school was almost obliterated by the start of the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think they did not run regular examinations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If you left somewhere after the midpoint of the year, you got credit for the year even though you learned very, very little in those days.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that happened to me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Within, I think, a month of the outbreak of war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was signed up for the Navy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was I don't think at that time even registered for the draft, but I was a volunteer.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, because otherwise I wouldn't have started Japanese three months before that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was fairly aware of the fact that the Japanese were militaristic and expansion-minded, and the United States was cramping their style.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
